wallpaper - command-line tool to set wallpaper using feh, written in haskell by alf

usage:
wallpaper [command] [args]

commands:
add [args]
	Add a favorite or a directory
	--favorite/-f 'num' 	- add a favorite, 'num' corresponds to the recent list
	--dir/-d 'path'	- add a directory, 'path' is the absolute path to the directory that should be added

list [args]
	List wallpapers, numbering corresponds to set/clear commands (read below)
	--all/-a 	lists all available wallpapers
	--recent/-r	lists recent wallpapers
	--favorite/-f	lists favorite wallpapers
	--dir/-d	list directories currently added

set [args]
	Set a wallpaper
	no args - equivalent to `wallpaper set --random`
	--random		set a random wallpaper from a directory supplied
	--favorite/-f 'num' 	set favorite number 'num' (see list), if num is ommited, it choses a random wallpaper from favorites
	--recent/-r 'num' 	set recent number 'num'

clear [args]
	--favorite/-f 'num'	- clear favorite number 'num', without 'num' it clears all of them
	--recent/-r		- clears all recent
	--dir/-d 'num'		..
